<p>I have this query to select the data from my database.</p>  <pre><code>SELECT monthname(DATA), sum(val1) DESPESAS, sum(val2) RECEITAS     from (      SELECT DATA, val1, val2          from (SELECT DATA, loja_id, valor val1, 0 val2               from despesas WHERE YEAR(DATA) = YEAR(CURDATE()) AND loja_id = '1') s1             union            (SELECT DATA loja_id, 0 val1, valor val2              from receitas WHERE YEAR(DATA) = YEAR(CURDATE()) and loja_id = '1') ) t     group by month(DATA)     order by DATA </code></pre>  <p>And it return the total sum of months in a table like this:</p>  <pre><code>MES         -       DESPESAS         -      RECEITAS January     -       R$16,29          -     R$355,00 February    -       R$120,00         -     R$107,29 March       -       R$124,06         -     R$0,00 April       -       R$0,00           -     R$38,00 May         -       R$130,91         -     R$37,00 July         -      R$0,00           -     R$10,00 </code></pre>  <p>How can I generate a chart with google chart with this values:</p>  <pre><code>cols = months and line 1 = despesas line 2 - receitas </code></pre>  <p>i'm generating manually like this</p>  <pre><code> google.setOnLoadCallback(drawChart);   function drawChart() {     var data = google.visualization.arrayToDataTable([     ['Mes', 'Receitas', 'Despesas'],     ['Janeiro',  0,      0],     ['Fevereiro',  0,      0],     ['Mar√ßo',  1315.98,       0],     ['Abril',  1066.08,      0],     ['Maio',  1764.04,      0],     ['Junho',  1875.59,      181.46],     ['Julho',  1850.54,      2102.84],     ['Agosto',  2980,      2527.6],     ['Setembro',  0,      0],     ['Outubro',  0,      0],     ['Novembro',  0,      0],     ['Dezembro',  0,      0]     ]);      var options = {       title: 'Despesas e Receitas Almirante',       hAxis: {title: 'Mes',  titleTextStyle: {color: '#333'}},       vAxis: {minValue: 0},       series: {         0: { color: '#0000FF' },         1: { color: '#FF0000' },       }     };      var chart = new google.visualization.AreaChart(document.getElementById('chart_Almirante'));     chart.draw(data, options);   } </code></pre>